#Text=Federico di Sanseverino
#Text=Federico di Sanseverino
#Text=( died 1516 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic cardinal of the 16th century .
#Text=Biography
#Text=Federico di Sanseverino was born in Naples in 1475 or 1477 .
#Text=He was the son of Roberto Sanseverino d'Aragona , a general of the papal army , and his second wife Elisabetta da Montefeltro . [ 1 ]
#Text=Early in his career , he was a cleric in Milan before becoming a protonotary apostolic . [ 1 ]

#Text=On November 5 , 1481 , he became the apostolic administrator of the see of Maillezais and occupied that post until 1508 . [ 1 ] Around 1492 , he became provost of the church of Santa Maria in Crescenzago . [ 1 ]
#Text=He was the apostolic administrator of the see of Novara from May 30 , 1505 until October 24 , 1511 . [ 1 ]
#Text=In the consistory of March 9 , 1489 , Pope Innocent VIII made him a cardinal deacon in pectore . [ 1 ]
#Text=Because of his youth , his creation was not published during the lifetime of Innocent VIII . [ 1 ]

#Text=During the sede vacante following the death of Innocent VIII , Cardinal Ascanio Sforza convinced the College of Cardinals to publish Sanseverino 's creation on July 26 , 1492 , and he received the deaconry of San Teodoro . [ 1 ]
#Text=He was therefore able to participate in the papal conclave of 1492 that elected Pope Alexander VI . [ 1 ]
#Text=In November 1494 , the new pope sent Cardinal Sanseverino as papal legate to Charles VIII of France in Siena . [ 1 ]
#Text=He returned quickly to Rome , where his loyalty was suspected by the pope . [ 1 ]

#Text=In order to frighten the rebels of Ostia , Cardinal Sanseverino and Cardinal Bernardino Lunati were arrested following the consistory of December 10 , 1494 , and held in the Apostolic Palace until December 19 , 1494 . [ 1 ]
#Text=He was then sent again as legate to Charles VIII ; he subsequently accompanied the French king on his entrance to Rome on December 31 , 1494 . [ 1 ]
#Text=He traveled with the pope to Orvieto on May 27 , 1495 and returned to Rome with the pontiff on June 27 . [ 1 ]
#Text=On February 8 , 1496 , he became apostolic administrator of the see of Thérouanne , occupying this post until November 12 , 1498 . [ 1 ]
#Text=On July 1 , 1497 , he became apostolic administrator of the see of Vienne and held this office until January 26 , 1515 . [ 1 ]
#Text=On August 3 , 1499 , he left , with the pope 's permission , for Milan to join Cardinal Ascanio Sforza . [ 1 ]
#Text=He participated in the papal conclave of September 1503 that elected Pope Pius III . [ 1 ]
#Text=He also participated in the papal conclave of October 1503 that elected Pope Julius II . [ 1 ]
#Text=On May 24 , 1504 , Pope Julius II named him papal legate to the Patrimonium Sancti Petri .
#Text=He became apostolic administrator of the see of Novara on May 30 , 1505 . [ 1 ]
#Text=On May 1 , 1510 , he opted for the deaconry of Sant'Angelo in Pescheria , while continuing to hold the deaconry of San Teodoro in commendam . [ 1 ]
#Text=After the pope threatened to imprison Cardinal Sanseverino in the Castel Sant'Angelo in June 1510 , the cardinal joined the pope 's enemies . [ 1 ]
#Text=In October 1510 , he sought refuge , with another four cardinals , in the camp of the French army and went to Milan . [ 1 ]
#Text=There , on May 16 , 1511 , he was one of the signatories of a document calling a council in Pisa for September 1 , 1511 . [ 1 ]
#Text=He did not attend this council after the pope threatened him with excommunication . [ 1 ]

#Text=He was present with the French forces at the Battle of Ravenna ( 1512 ) ; Louis XII of France planned to make Cardinal Sanseverino governor of the Papal States after deposing the pope , but this never came to pass . [ 1 ]
#Text=Following the death of Pope Julius II , Cardinal Sanseverino did not participate in the papal conclave of 1513 that elected Pope Leo X . [ 1 ]
#Text=Shortly thereafter the cardinal was arrested in Florence on the pope 's orders , with a promise he would be released if he repented . [ 1 ]
#Text=On June 17 , 1513 , he denounced the schismatical council of Pisa and submitted to the pope 's authority in a letter later read at a session of the Fifth Council of the Lateran . [ 1 ]
#Text=He and Cardinal Bernardino López de Carvajal arrived in Rome on June 27 , 1513 and personally repented in a secret consistory held in Rome . [ 1 ]
#Text=He was absolved by the pope , ordered to fast for a month , and restored to the College of Cardinals . [ 1 ]
#Text=From June 1513 , he was the cardinal protodeacon . [ 1 ]
#Text=Shortly later , he was named cardinal protector of the Kingdom of France . [ 1 ]
#Text=On June 25 , 1515 , he was arrested on the pope 's orders because it looked like one of his servants had killed a papal guard , but he proved his innocence the next day . [ 1 ]
#Text=In November 1515 , he was sent as a papal legate to Francis I of France , who met him outside the gates of Bologna . [ 1 ]
#Text=He died in Rome on August 7 , 1516 . [ 1 ]
#Text=He is buried in Santa Maria in Aracoeli . [ 1 ]
